OL,3,CFuneral directors left 46 bodies to
OL,4,Cdecompose in unrefrigerated conditions
OL,6,FThe discovery was made when bailiffs,
OL,7,Fsent in by creditors, found two bodies
OL,8,Fstored in a room with water leaking
OL,9,Fthrough the ceiling.
OL,11,FOne had been left for 36 days and was
OL,12,Ffound in a badly decomposed condition.
OL,13,FHe was an elderly gentleman, whose
OL,14,Ffamily had arrived at a crematorium
OL,15,Fbelieving their loved one had been
OL,16,Fcremated to find out that in fact his
OL,17,Fbody remained at the funeral
OL,18,Fdirectors' premises.
