OL,6,FThey were both found guilty of
OL,7,Fintentionally causing public nuisance
OL,8,Fbetween June 27 2022 and December 11
OL,9,F2023, preventing lawful burial of a
OL,10,Fbody between November 3 2023 and
OL,11,FDecember 11 2023 and carrying on a
OL,12,Fbusiness fraudulently between August
OL,13,F10 2022 and December 11 2023.
OL,15,FElkin was also convicted of the
OL,16,Fforgery of a certificate of funeral
OL,17,Fdirecting and using it as a false
OL,18,Fcertificate on or before December 10
OL,19,F2023. He also previously pleaded
OL,20,Fguilty to illegal possession of pepper
OL,21,Fspray.
