OL,3,CFuneral directors left 46 bodies to
OL,4,Cdecompose in unrefrigerated conditions
OL,6,F"They showed a grave disregard for the
OL,7,Fdignity owed to the deceased in their
OL,8,Fcare and the trust placed in them by
OL,9,Fgrieving families and failed to
OL,10,Fprovide a proper and lawful burial for
OL,11,Fone gentleman which they were
OL,12,Fcontractually obliged to do. Their
OL,13,Fconduct caused serious harm to those
OL,14,Fcoming into contact with their
OL,15,Fbusiness and the families who had
OL,16,Fplaced the care of deceased loved ones
OL,17,Fin their trust.
